<statement>
<image width="33%"  pi:generated="problems/images/83b768d4b4b1e408642694c2fc57e5d8.png" /><p>
Suppose a = 4 and A = 25 degrees. Calculate:</p>
<p>
b = <fillin characters="20" /></p>
<p>
c = <fillin characters="20" /></p>
<p>
B = <fillin characters="20" /> degrees</p>
<p>
Round all answers to one decimal place.  Give angles in <em>degrees</em>
</p>
</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li>8.6</li><li>9.5</li><li>65.0</li></ul></p><p>First calculate the length of the other leg.</p>
<p>For the length of the other leg,</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{\tan{{\left({25}\right)}}}=\frac{{4}}{{b}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{b}=\frac{{4}}{{\tan{{\left({25}\right)}}}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{b}\approx{8.5780276820382}\approx{8.6}</m>.</p>
<p>For the third side</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}^{{2}}={4}^{{2}}+{8.5780276820382}^{{2}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}^{{2}}={16}+{73.582558913814}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}^{{2}}={89.582558913814}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}=\sqrt{{{89.582558913814}}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}\approx{9.46480633261}\approx{9.5}</m>.</p>
<p>For angle B</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{B}={180}^{\circ}-{90}^{\circ}-{25}^{\circ}\approx{65}^{\circ}</m></p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>

